<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Well, it starts with a description of two very young kids seeing a dead body, then goes on to describe how grandma takes advantage of this death to me<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">â€¦more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Well, it starts with a description of two very young kids seeing a dead body, then goes on to describe how grandma takes advantage of this death to mess with her enemy and make herself look good and then force the kids to see said body. There is lying, cheating, and all sorts of problems. I don't call that appropriate!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link615457" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=615457&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F846314-is-it-appropriate%2Fanswers%2F615457-well-it-starts-with-a">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

</div>
</div>

